<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n14022b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n14" href="#n14022b">N14 (VI.B.7)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n14all.htm#n14022b"> 22(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> her place in / the dark</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">For, as Germany has hitherto striven for material riches, striven to maintain the outward bulwarks of her so-called culture, struggled to maintain her supremacy in trade and manufacture, in industry and mechanics, and as she has fought to maintain <mark>her &ldquo;place in the sun</mark>,&rdquo; so will she now turn her energies and bend her will to acquiring the riches of the spirit&mdash;those <i>inner</i> bulwarks of her civilization, and of her German Christianity&mdash;to the end that she may establish and retain the power of her position in Science, Art, Morality, and Justice, as applied to life, doing so against every &ldquo;ism&rdquo; in the world. <small> Ernst Boldt, <a name="BFLS" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BFLS"><cite title="source">From Luther to Steiner</cite></a>, (1921) xiv</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
